    <briefdescription>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>This is an unpleasant case, like the <ref refid="classStochSecondOrderSingleSubstrate" kindref="compound">StochSecondOrderSingleSubstrate</ref>. Here we deal with the possibility that one or more of the substrates may be of order greater than one. If so, we need to diminish the N of each substrate by one for each time the substrate is factored into the rate. </para>
    </detaileddescription>
